96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.09e34c3c-179a-4b04-8138-5326b0fd6451.prompt=Delimiter\: 96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.1e113752-6804-4f14-acae-47f44554f127.prompt=Enter a value for matchTo 96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.1f514aba-01ae-423c-9979-c3cb71cd3d23.prompt=Delimiter\: 96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.2d9adf10-8aba-483c-b4cd-803973114934.prompt=String to Append \: 96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.33c9536e-1f19-449a-9079-177e527c2383.prompt=Enter a value for toMatch 96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.36758bb5-ae51-4f18-ac48-f67315295af0.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.aa51d0ec-5cf3-4d65-b503-c17afd9a8f8e.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.

96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match to the value specified in the input "compareTo" based on the input "matchType".  

Inputs\:
list - The list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Results\:
others -  A delimiter delimited list of elements that do not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
96dbee54-cf5a-4395-8bea-a00aa340457d.fe960802-168a-4a99-bd47-2e71da6e31a0.description=Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration..
